5: Excuse me, are you all right?
8:
Ah, you're that girl that was lost the
other day... Nieve, was it?
18:
That's what everyone's saying! There
have been sightings and everything!
20:
But my big sister just laughs
whenever I bring it up. She says
dragons aren't real...
23: Hmm... What do you think, Alk?
27:
I'm pretty sure dragons don't exist in
this world.
30:
I thought as much... I can imagine
sea serpents and the like, but I
cannot fathom where a dragon
would make its nest in this landless
world.
33:
That being said... The fact that there
are sightings means there must be
SOMETHING out there... Dragon or
not.
36:
...Or it could be complete hearsay
and we find nothing... Either way...
43:
It looks like we'll be having ourselves
a dragon hunt!
46:
If you think there's a dragon, then I
will help you track them down. How
does that sound?
49:
Azel is an expert when it comes to
dealing with dragons.
52:
Really? Then yeah, let's find the
dragon! Thank you, Mr. Azel!
55:
You sure about this? What if it turns
out there is no dragon...
59:
Either way, I'm sure Nieve will learn a
lot from this experience.
62:
And... I must admit I find myself
intrigued.
68:
Our hunt should begin with some
preliminary research.
70:
We should first confirm what we can
about the rumors by looking
through newspaper archives and
researching old legends... Think you
can handle that?
75:
Um... If we find the dragon, do you
think it'll be my friend?
77:
...Dragons are volatile creatures.
Many have been known to attack
civilians.
80:
However, just because MANY are
dangerous, doesn't mean they ALL
are. An important distinction to
make.
82:
Nieve... Can you promise me that
you will never forget that desire for
friendship?
88:
Then I'm sure you'll make friends
with a dragon someday.
94:
According to Nieve's research, this
should be the spot where an
unidentified creature was spotted...
Correct?
97:
Yup! This is the place! But... I don't
see anything...
100:
Worry not, Nieve. I'm sure your
research will bear fruit.
104:
But it's getting late... Perhaps we
should withdraw for toda
122: Halt, beast! I shall be your opponent!
126:
Azel! We fought a dragon like this in
the casino! This one must be a
survivor!
130:
So in other words, I don't have to
hold back!
152:
I was wondering when you'd get
here...
156:
Was I too heavy-handed for your
liking, Azel?
160:
It doesn't matter, as long as Nieve is
safe and sound. She's not exactly
accustomed to combat.
164:
Besides, I'm overjoyed at the chance
to see your lightning again, Rams
Euphoria.
167: Mr. Azel... Who's this pretty dragon?
170:
This is the dragon that saved my
life... And who taught me that
coexistence is possible.
174:
Good evening, little one. I am Rams,
one of the Ancients and an ally to
these fine people.
177:
Whoa... So you guys were friends
with a dragon the whole time! Cool!
180:
Friends... Hehe... I suppose so. Would
you also like to be friends with me,
child?
186: See? Your dream came true, didn't it?
189:
Yeah! Just like you said it would...
Thank you, Mr. Azel!
192:
Haha, no need to thank me, Nieve.
This was all your handiwork.
195:
Friends with a dragon, eh... That has
a nice ring to it.
